com.github.robtimus.obfuscation.annotation

Annotation Type ObfuscatePortion


  • @Documented
 @Target(value={ANNOTATION_TYPE,FIELD,METHOD,PARAMETER})
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface ObfuscatePortion
    Indicates that obfuscation should be done in a similar way to using Obfuscator.portion().
    Author:
    Rob Spoor

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      int atLeastFromEnd
      The minimum number of characters from the end that need to be obfuscated.
      int atLeastFromStart
      The minimum number of characters from the start that need to be obfuscated.
      int fixedLength
      The fixed number of mask characters, or a negative value to use the actual length.
      int keepAtEnd
      The number of characters to skip at the end.
      int keepAtStart
      The number of characters to skip at the start.
      char maskChar
      The character to replace with.

        public abstract int keepAtStart
        The number of characters to skip at the start.

        public abstract int atLeastFromEnd
